This paper is about speech recognition, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which specifically deals with NLP tasks. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Additionally, the paper involves optimization of the model, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of a second-pass component also involves the use of attention mechanisms, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with latency constraints, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
